description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This is an opportunity for an enthusiastic and hard working individual to join the Dermatology department Bristol Royal Infirmary.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Working as part of a large team in a busy environment, you will draw on your experience and skills to effectively communicate with colleagues, clinicians and peers to support the effective management of a range of administrative tasks.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Key experience you will need to apply for the role:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Ability to use initiative and manage your own workload&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- The ability to communicate both via telephone and in writing&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- Appetite to learn and develop&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;- IT literate. Previous experience using Medway or other patient administration system is desirable&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Due to high volumes of applications, vacancies may be closed before the closing date.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Permanent position available as follows;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;1 x Part Time, 19.5 hours (Wednesday - Friday ideally) - MDT Patient Tracker&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Full role details can be found in the job description.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name India Galdies&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title Team Leader&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address India.Galdies@uhbw.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
